{
  "texts": [
    "Lastly, we recommend embedding participatory AI design practices into public procurement criteria, ensuring that solutions funded or adopted by public actors are inclusive and socially grounded.",
    "To support just and context-aware AI deployment in climate resilience, we propose a framework inspired by recent work from Jain et al. (2024a,b).",
    "Their studies demonstrate that equitable AI implementation requires not only technical innovation but deep engagement with local realities, especially in climate-vulnerable and resource-constrained regions.",
    "Jain et al. (2024a) highlight how embedding AI and machine learning in South Asia's water-energy-food systems succeeds only when local capacity is developed and interdisciplinary collaboration is fostered.",
    "Similarly, Jain et al. (2024b) emphasize that inclusive design-drawing on indigenous and local knowledge-and strong policy alignment are essential to ensure AI solutions are ethically grounded and responsive to local needs."
  ]
}